Key Match Events: Shohei Ohtani hit a go-ahead single in a five-run seventh inning.
Will Smith had a game-tying two-run homer.
Mookie Betts added a two-run single in the seventh inning.
Freddie Freeman departed in the seventh inning after rolling his right ankle.
Luis Arraez and Xander Bogaerts each drove in a run for the Padres.
Walker Buehler gave up one run on five hits over five innings.
Anthony Banda pitched 1⅓ scoreless innings for the win.
Joe Musgrove gave up two runs on five hits over 6⅓ innings.
Tanner Scott was charged with three runs in two-thirds of an inning.
David Peralta drew a one-out walk and went to third on a double by Kyle Higashioka.
Jurickson Profar singled and eventually scored on a sacrifice fly by Xander Bogaerts.
Max Muncy worked a leadoff walk and Smith hit a game-tying home run.
Enrique Hernandez had a pinch-hit single.
Andy Pages was awarded first base on catcher's interference.
Ohtani hit a slow roller into right field for a 3-2 lead.
Betts followed with his two-run double.
Pages hit a two-run home run for the Dodgers in the eighth inning.
